        <head xml:id="pl-l4d3c8-Hd1e109">CAP. VIII</head>
        <head xml:id="pl-l4d3c8-Hd1e112" type="question-title">
          When circumcision lost its power
        </head>
        <p xml:id="pl-l4d3c8-d1e115">
          It is customary to ask, 
          if circumcision lost its status 
          from the institution of baptism.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="pl-l4d3c8-d1e118">
          To this question we say, 
          in the death of Christ all legal obligations were terminated. 
          From then on therefore 
          circumcision lost its power, 
          such that afterwards it no longer had an effect, 
          rather it became an obstacle to those who observed it, 
          but up until the time of the presentation of the true 
          it was able to be of use. 
          For if before the passion 
          legal matter were to come to an end, 
          the disciples would not, 
          while the passion was imminent,
          have been eating the old passover mean.
        </p>
      </div>
